
[1]portentous

   PORTENT'OUS, a. [L. portentosus.] Ominous; foreshowing ill. Ignorance
   and superstition hold meteors to be portentous.

   1. Monstrous; prodigious; wonderful; in an ill sense.

   No beast of more portentous size,

   In the Hercynian forest lies.
